        "comments": "bind(e, f) is the monadic bind for either with a fixed Left type: if e is Right v, the result is f(v); if e is Left x, the result is Left x with the Left type preserved. Total. Used to chain computations that may fail with a common error type. Corresponds to Haskell's (>>=) :: Either a b -> (b -> Either a c) -> Either a c.",
        "defaultImplementation": {
          "annotated": {
            "annotation": [{"key": "description", "value": {"literal": {"string": "Monadic bind for Either, defined in terms of either."}}}],
