          "typeParameters": [{"constraints": [], "name": "x"}, {"constraints": [], "name": "y"}, {"constraints": [], "name": "z"}]}}},
    {
      "primitive": {
        "comments": "either(f, g, e) returns f(x) if e is Left x and g(y) if e is Right y. The fundamental eliminator for the either type; every other primitive in this namespace can be derived from it. Total. Corresponds to Haskell's either :: (a -> c) -> (b -> c) -> Either a b -> c.",
        "description": "Eliminate an either value by applying one of two functions.",
        "isPure": true,
        "isTotal": true,
        "name": "hydra.lib.eithers.either",
        "seeAlso": [],
        "signature": {
          "parameters": [
            {"isLazy": false, "name": "arg0", "type": {"function": {"codomain": {"variable": "z"}, "domain": {"variable": "x"}}}},
